node.text:
Thank you @macygray for asking me to ⭐️ in this fabulous music video. It is such an honor and I love you. Thank you to our amazing director @donguidof and my HMU angel @hyewonahn & the choreographer @sarahaliceburns & the production geniuses at
@chokolatemmm! I was extremely excited for this role and this project. Macy and I spoke about this gorgeous song and the message she was hoping to convey about how unrequited love can cause a person to become undone, as well as her vision for me to be in drag. I immediately gravitated toward the concept. As we discussed the character, a man who felt his parter did not accept him as he came to love himself in the world, I was able to step into those heels and live out loud. I hope that when you see this video you will be inspired to live your truth no matter what society or a partner says, because it is when we are standing in our authentic self that we are happiest and unstoppable.

node.text:
Taking over Frankie’s account as a part of #TransTakeOver, founded by @ashleemariepreston! 

Tiiiiny bit about me:
I am an artist who identifies Deaf, trans, Jewish, and Chinese. My background includes launching a clothing line with Opening Ceremony, writing as a columnist for Condé Naste’s first queer publication - @Them, and being casted as a queer superhero within Warner Brother’s DC Universe, Titans.

Giving this talk two years ago felt as if I was opening up my diary and reading it to a crowd. It pinpoints three revelations I reached at the beginning of my gender journey.

I would love to know what you think about it!

ps: I answer your most curious questions on Frankie’s Instagram story today ;) #TransgenderAwarenessWeek

node.text: I don’t truly have words to express how much this woman means to me. She has shown me nothing but unconditional love my entire life and in return I have loved her with all my heart. Happy birthday to my amazing Nonna! Enjoy this magical day of celebrating you. What a milestone! The entire world is honoring you today. 👑🎂🥳💖

node.text:
Thank you @macygray for asking me to ⭐️ in this fabulous music video. It is such an honor and I love you. Thank you to our amazing director @donguidof and my HMU angel @hyewonahn & the choreographer @sarahaliceburns & the production geniuses at
@chokolatemmm! I was extremely excited for this role and this project. Macy and I spoke about this gorgeous song and the message she was hoping to convey about how unrequited love can cause a person to become undone, as well as her vision for me to be in drag. I immediately gravitated toward the concept. As we discussed the character, a man who felt his parter did not accept him as he came to love himself in the world, I was able to step into those heels and live out loud. I hope that when you see this video you will be inspired to live your truth no matter what society or a partner says, because it is when we are standing in our authentic self that we are happiest and unstoppable.
